{"nodes":[{"content":"Use list view or grid view controls to display and manipulate sets of data, such as a gallery of images or a set of email messages.","pos":[32,163]},{"content":"List view and grid view","pos":[171,194]},{"content":"ListView and GridView","pos":[253,274]},{"content":"Most applications manipulate and display sets of data, such as a gallery of images or a set of email messages.","pos":[276,386]},{"content":"The XAML UI framework provides ListView and GridView controls that make it easy to display and manipulate data in your app.","pos":[387,510]},{"content":"ListView and GridView both derive from the ListViewBase class, so they have the same functionality, but display data differently.","pos":[514,643]},{"content":"In this article, when we talk about ListView, the info applies to both the ListView and GridView controls unless otherwise specified.","pos":[644,777]},{"content":"We may refer to classes like ListView or ListViewItem, but the “List” prefix can be replaced with “Grid” for the corresponding grid equivalent (GridView or GridViewItem).","pos":[778,948]},{"pos":[1008,1022],"content":"Important APIs"},{"content":"ListView class","pos":[1038,1052]},{"content":"GridView class","pos":[1151,1165]},{"content":"ItemsSource property","pos":[1264,1284]},{"content":"ItemTemplate property","pos":[1399,1420]},{"content":"Is this the right control?","pos":[1533,1559]},{"content":"The ListView displays data stacked vertically in a single column.","pos":[1561,1626]},{"content":"It's often used to show an ordered list of items, such as a list of emails or search results.","pos":[1627,1720]},{"content":"It's also useful in <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>master-detail<ept id=\"p1\">](master-details.md)</ept> scenarios, where the list items contain only a small amount of info and the details of the selected item are shown separately.","pos":[1721,1902]},{"content":"Example of a master-details pattern","pos":[1907,1942]},{"content":"The GridView presents a collection of items in rows and columns that can scroll vertically.","pos":[1994,2085]},{"content":"Data is stacked horizontally until it fills the columns, then continues with the next row.","pos":[2086,2176]},{"content":"It's often used when you need to show a rich visualization of each item that takes more space, such as a photo gallery.","pos":[2177,2296]},{"content":"Example of a content library","pos":[2301,2329]},{"pos":[2373,2464],"content":"For a more detailed comparison and guidance on which control to use, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Lists<ept id=\"p1\">](lists.md)</ept>."},{"content":"Create a list view","pos":[2469,2487]},{"content":"List view is an <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ItemsControl<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/windows.ui.xaml.controls.itemscontrol.aspx)</ept>, so it can contain a collection of items of any type.","pos":[2489,2665]},{"content":"It must have items in its <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Items<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept><ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/windows.ui.xaml.controls.itemscontrol.items.aspx)</ept> collection before it can show anything on the screen.","pos":[2666,2855]},{"content":"To populate the view, you can add items directly to the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Items<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept><ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/windows.ui.xaml.controls.itemscontrol.items.aspx)</ept> collection, or set the <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>ItemsSource<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept><ept id=\"p3\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/windows.ui.xaml.controls.itemscontrol.itemssource.aspx)</ept> property to a data source.","pos":[2856,3193]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Important<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>You can use either Items or ItemsSource to populate the list, but you can't use both at the same time.","pos":[3196,3323]},{"content":"If you set the ItemsSource propert