</ph>) on the DataTemplate.","pos":[8747,8975]},{"content":"To set <ph id=\"ph1\">`x:DataType=\"System:String\"`</ph>, as in this example, you have to add the <ph id=\"ph2\">`xmlns:System=\"using:System\"`</ph> <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>XAML namespace declaration<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/windows/uwp/xaml-platform/xaml-overview#xaml-namespaces)</ept> to your Page.","pos":[8976,9209]},{"content":"XAML","pos":[9213,9217]},{"content":"Here's what the data items look like when displayed with this data template.","pos":[10032,10108]},{"content":"List view items with a data template","pos":[10112,10148]},{"content":"Data templates are the primary way you define the look of your list view.","pos":[10186,10259]},{"content":"They can also have a significant impact on performance if your list displays a large number of items.","pos":[10260,10361]},{"content":"In this article, we use simple string data for most of the examples, and don't specify a data template.","pos":[10362,10465]},{"content":"For more info and examples of how to use DataTemplates and item containers to define the look of items in your list or grid, see <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Modify the look of list items<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.","pos":[10466,10627]},{"content":"Change the layout of items","pos":[10633,10659]},{"content":"When you add items to a list view or grid view, the control automatically wraps each item in an item container and then lays out all of the item containers.","pos":[10661,10817]},{"content":"How these item containers are laid out depends on the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>ItemsPanel<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept><ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/windows.ui.xaml.controls.itemscontrol.itemspanel.aspx)</ept> of the control.","pos":[10818,11007]},{"pos":[11012,11205],"content":"By default, <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ListView<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> uses an <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>ItemsStackPanel<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept><ept id=\"p